x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-Functional/Basic Requirements-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x

1)The user should be able to select from our database of ingredients, according to the ones they have in their kitchen.
2)The user should be able to see a range of different recipes that use the ingredients they have in their kitchen.
3)The user should be able to select a checkbox if they want “Healthier recipes”.
4)The user should be able to select what type of diet they want. (Vegetarian, vegan, halal, etc) or if they are fine with any.
5)The user should be able to open each recipe individually.

x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-Non-functional Requirements-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x

1)Interface - Should be intuitive and easy to use.
2)Server-side optimization for faster performance/smooth user experience.
3)Scalability - an algorithm with a low time complexity.
4)Maintainability - good quality code, easy to change
5)Deployment- The website should be in a deployable form.
6)Platform Compatibility: Optimized for web apps on a computer or smartphone.

x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-User-Interface Requirements-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x

1)Website should involve colours that not too vibrant or bright but pleasant to the eye for better viewing experiences.
2)The interface should have simple English and not involve any technical jargon.
3)The user interface should be able to work properly on most regularly  used laptop resolutions
4)The user interface must have a responsive ingredient search bar.
5)The user interface must provide organised results.
6)The user interface should allow the user to select diets easily in an organised way
7) The user interface should display information regarding a recipe that can be understood easily.
8)The website should have buttons which simplify navigation
9)The button with text on the website should be distinguishable from other texts on web page with well designed interaction styles
10) The user interface must have a user's navigation help guide (FAQ).
